==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Esurient
<hw>E*su"ri*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>esuriens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>ensurire</ets>, fr. <ets>edere</ets>
to eat.]</ety> <def>Inclined to eat; hungry; voracious.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <au>Bailey.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Poor, but
<xex>esurient</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Esurient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Esurient
<hw>E*su"ri*ent</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is hungry or
greedy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An insatiable <qex>esurient</qex> after riches.</q>
<rj><qau>Wood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Esurine</ent>⟦br⟧
